{"subgoals":[{"name":"enter_first_yellow_cluster","predicate_src":"def predicate(frame)->bool:
    # Blue/player cells have reached or touched the upper-left yellow cluster inside the maze.
    ys, xs = np.where(frame == 8)
    if len(xs) == 0:
        return False
    target = (slice(8, 14), slice(14, 20))
    return np.any(frame[target] == 8) or np.any((ys >= 7) & (ys <= 14) & (xs >= 13) & (xs <= 20))"},{"name":"clear_first_yellow_cluster","predicate_src":"def predicate(frame)->bool:
    # The initial upper-left cluster of 9s has been removed/converted.
    region = frame[8:14, 14:20]
    return np.count_nonzero(region == 9) == 0"},{"name":"enter_second_yellow_cluster","predicate_src":"def predicate(frame)->bool:
    # Blue/player cells have reached or touched the lower-right yellow cluster.
    ys, xs = np.where(frame == 8)
    if len(xs) == 0:
        return False
    return np.any((ys >= 50) & (ys <= 58) & (xs >= 42) & (xs <= 51))"},{"name":"clear_second_yellow_cluster","predicate_src":"def predicate(frame)->bool:
    # The lower-right 9 cluster has been removed/converted while ignoring the bottom border of 9s.
    region = frame[50:59, 42:52]
    return np.count_nonzero(region == 9) == 0"},{"name":"all_interior_yellow_cleared","predicate_src":"def predicate(frame)->bool:
    # Goal hypothesis: collect/erase all interior yellow 9s; the all-9 bottom row is a boundary, not a target.
    interior = frame[:63, :]
    return np.count_nonzero(interior == 9) == 0"}],"macros":[[[4],[4],[4],[4],[4]],[[2],[2],[2],[2],[2],[2],[2],[2]],[[3],[3],[3],[3],[3],[3],[3],[3]],[[1],[1],[1],[1],[1]],[[5]]],"score_fn_src":"def score_fn(frame)->float:
    # Higher when fewer interior yellow targets remain and blue/player is closer to the nearest remaining target.
    yellow = np.argwhere(frame[:63, :] == 9)
    blue = np.argwhere(frame == 8)
    if yellow.size == 0:
        return 100000.0
    remaining = float(len(yellow))
    if blue.size == 0:
        return -1000.0 - remaining
    d = np.abs(blue[:, None, :] - yellow[None, :, :]).sum(axis=2).min()
    return -100.0 * remaining - float(d)","rationale":"The visible maze contains two interior clusters of color 9 embedded in/near traversable color 5, while color 8 appears to be the controllable moving trail/player. The bottom all-9 row looks like a border or hazard, so the inferred goal is to navigate the 8 region to the interior 9 clusters and clear/collect them."}

